1
00:00:34,904 --> 00:00:36,067
[This drama is fictional
and bears no resemblance to reality]

2
00:00:36,067 --> 00:00:37,010
[Some scenes feature AI technology]

3
00:00:37,010 --> 00:00:38,102
[All child and animal scenes
followed strict safety guidelines]

4
00:00:44,796 --> 00:00:48,547
[Episode 4]
<i>♪ Why am I standing on this road? ♪</i>

5
00:00:48,547 --> 00:00:52,487
<i>♪ Is this really my path? ♪</i>

6
00:00:52,487 --> 00:00:54,691
<i>♪ At the end of this road ♪</i>

7
00:00:54,691 --> 00:00:59,572
<i>♪ Will my dream come true? ♪</i>

8
00:00:59,572 --> 00:01:04,083
<i>♪ I want to say with confidence
that this is my path ♪</i>

9
00:01:04,083 --> 00:01:06,398
- Hey, hey.
<i>- ♪ Never regret it... ♪</i>

10
00:01:12,451 --> 00:01:16,368
You think you're walking straight?

11
00:01:16,368 --> 00:01:18,693
What's that supposed to mean?

12
00:01:18,693 --> 00:01:20,799
Because I got fired?

13
00:01:20,799 --> 00:01:22,662
No, that's not it.

14
00:01:22,662 --> 00:01:26,102
Where are you going? What road is this?

15
00:01:26,102 --> 00:01:28,420
Same road as you.

16
00:01:28,420 --> 00:01:29,756
What?

17
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:32,482
I'm making movies with you.

18
00:01:44,036 --> 00:01:48,244
<i>- ♪ What am I dreaming of... ♪</i>
- Hey, hey! Wait!

19
00:01:48,244 --> 00:01:51,776
<i>♪ Who is that dream really for? ♪</i>

20
00:01:51,776 --> 00:01:56,172
<i>♪ If I make it come true,
will I finally smile... ♪</i>

21
00:02:21,633 --> 00:02:22,681
Gosh.

22
00:02:23,327 --> 00:02:24,519
What the...

23
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:26,935
You're insane, Ju Yi Jae!

24
00:02:44,928 --> 00:02:46,618
Ian.

25
00:02:53,228 --> 00:02:54,873
What?

26
00:02:55,521 --> 00:02:57,119
- Someone's here.
- Ian?

27
00:02:57,119 --> 00:02:59,295
Let's go get some breakfast.

28
00:02:59,982 --> 00:03:01,834
In Uk.

29
00:03:07,546 --> 00:03:09,101
It's freezing.

30
00:03:10,142 --> 00:03:11,535
Huh?

31
00:03:16,128 --> 00:03:17,532
Are you in there?

32
00:03:17,532 --> 00:03:19,852
What are you doing?

33
00:03:19,852 --> 00:03:21,657
Yeah, I'm in the shower.

34
00:03:21,657 --> 00:03:23,075
Okay.

35
00:03:29,470 --> 00:03:31,614
Sounds like a rough shower.

36
00:03:31,614 --> 00:03:34,514
It'd be a problem if you died in there alone.

37
00:03:34,514 --> 00:03:37,580
For me, for the hotel...

38
00:03:37,580 --> 00:03:41,590
You too, probably. Going out like that.

39
00:03:42,405 --> 00:03:44,407
Or maybe...

40
00:03:44,407 --> 00:03:46,350
You'd be proud.

41
00:03:46,350 --> 00:03:48,013
You're hot.

42
00:03:48,013 --> 00:03:50,125
Come to the lounge.

43
00:04:21,950 --> 00:04:23,890
What were you thinking?

44
00:04:25,090 --> 00:04:27,248
I didn't know where to look.

45
00:04:27,248 --> 00:04:28,709
Your eyes?

46
00:04:30,388 --> 00:04:32,182
They're puffy.

47
00:04:51,154 --> 00:04:52,739
Hey!

48
00:04:52,739 --> 00:04:56,191
You should've told me you had a roommate.

49
00:04:56,191 --> 00:04:57,769
I did.

50
00:04:57,769 --> 00:05:00,971
He's next door, not my roommate.

51
00:05:00,971 --> 00:05:02,596
Wait outside.

52
00:05:02,596 --> 00:05:05,236
We need to talk about last night.

53
00:05:07,044 --> 00:05:08,817
Don't go.

54
00:05:37,221 --> 00:05:41,378
Normally, this is where the girl runs.

55
00:05:41,378 --> 00:05:42,672
But I'm different.

56
00:05:42,672 --> 00:05:44,868
Sounds rehearsed.

57
00:05:46,802 --> 00:05:48,885
How did I get here?

58
00:05:48,885 --> 00:05:51,765
I remember saying I'd make movies with you.

59
00:05:51,765 --> 00:05:54,134
Fill me in after that.

60
00:05:55,081 --> 00:05:58,608
So that's where you blacked out?

61
00:06:00,615 --> 00:06:04,572
I didn't know you were that bold.

62
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:05,716
"Bold?"

63
00:06:05,716 --> 00:06:07,192
Me?

64
00:06:08,315 --> 00:06:11,615
What exactly did I do?

65
00:06:12,455 --> 00:06:14,144
Ju Yi Jae.

66
00:06:14,798 --> 00:06:16,486
You listed your place.

67
00:06:16,486 --> 00:06:18,086
What?

68
00:06:20,378 --> 00:06:23,103
It's a bit old, but the layout is great.

69
00:06:23,103 --> 00:06:25,888
It faces south, so it gets great light.

70
00:06:26,535 --> 00:06:28,063
You're the tenant, right?

71
00:06:28,063 --> 00:06:30,309
- Hello.
- The landlord called me.

72
00:06:30,309 --> 00:06:32,947
You even gave us the door code.

73
00:06:32,947 --> 00:06:35,507
Thank you so much.

74
00:06:35,507 --> 00:06:36,893
I did?

75
00:06:36,893 --> 00:06:41,923
I've been running around all morning
just to show this place.

76
00:06:41,923 --> 00:06:45,907
<i>I really am... my own regret.</i>

77
00:06:47,775 --> 00:06:50,592
- I really like this place.
- Right?

78
00:06:50,592 --> 00:06:52,549
Look over here too.

79
00:06:54,342 --> 00:06:56,140
- Hello.
- Hi.

80
00:06:56,140 --> 00:06:57,830
- Hello.
- Hello.

81
00:06:57,830 --> 00:07:00,411
- Hello.
- Hello.

82
00:07:00,411 --> 00:07:01,917
Hello.

83
00:07:01,917 --> 00:07:03,693
Hello.

84
00:07:15,305 --> 00:07:17,769
[Film Screenplay and Directing Agreement]

85
00:07:22,025 --> 00:07:24,392
- Yi Jae.
- Yeah?

86
00:07:24,392 --> 00:07:27,575
Is that seal heavy?

87
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:31,143
A little.

88
00:07:31,143 --> 00:07:33,645
Mine felt heavy too on my first contract.

89
00:07:34,705 --> 00:07:39,594
Maybe try thinking of it another way.

90
00:07:41,597 --> 00:07:47,556
This isn't a world
where no one notices if you disappear.

91
00:07:47,556 --> 00:07:50,706
This story is yours.

92
00:07:50,706 --> 00:07:54,752
You started it, so you get to finish it.

93
00:07:54,752 --> 00:07:58,421
That means you write it and direct it.

94
00:07:59,379 --> 00:08:04,264
And I'll be with you the whole way.

95
00:08:04,264 --> 00:08:06,076
To the end.

96
00:08:14,584 --> 00:08:15,906
[Sealed by Ju Yi Jae]

97
00:08:17,557 --> 00:08:19,058
Finally.

98
00:08:19,966 --> 00:08:22,448
Now it really begins.

99
00:08:22,448 --> 00:08:23,992
Hello, I'm Seo In Uk.

100
00:08:23,992 --> 00:08:25,572
Hello.

101
00:08:25,572 --> 00:08:31,058
I'll do everything I can
so you can focus on the script.

102
00:08:31,058 --> 00:08:32,194
Thank you.

103
00:08:32,194 --> 00:08:33,896
What about the studio?

104
00:08:34,748 --> 00:08:38,201
She doesn't have a place right now.

105
00:08:38,201 --> 00:08:39,871
Why would you say that?

106
00:08:39,871 --> 00:08:42,225
So that's why you were at the hotel.

107
00:08:42,225 --> 00:08:45,216
- Sorry?
- I saw a pair of unfamiliar shoes.

108
00:08:45,216 --> 00:08:48,084
We just met but...

109
00:08:55,505 --> 00:08:57,172
I've seen your shoes.

110
00:09:02,065 --> 00:09:04,802
- I'm sorry.
- No need.

111
00:09:04,802 --> 00:09:08,989
We're looking for a quiet house nearby.

112
00:09:08,989 --> 00:09:11,032
He insisted on that area.

113
00:09:11,032 --> 00:09:14,945
Please stay at the hotel
just until the studio is set up.

114
00:09:14,945 --> 00:09:17,033
I can stay with a friend.

115
00:09:17,033 --> 00:09:19,229
I'm afraid I can't allow that.

116
00:09:19,229 --> 00:09:20,766
You need to write.

117
00:09:20,766 --> 00:09:22,878
The hotel will be better.

118
00:09:22,878 --> 00:09:26,311
- Yes, sir.
- I look forward to working with you.

119
00:09:27,994 --> 00:09:30,417
Same here.

120
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:40,837
Ta-da! Here Comes Dong Hyun!

121
00:09:40,837 --> 00:09:42,796
He's better.

122
00:09:43,470 --> 00:09:45,114
Welcome.

123
00:09:45,114 --> 00:09:46,920
You've got a good eye.

124
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:48,522
Perfect.

125
00:09:50,436 --> 00:09:53,353
- Producer Kyung?
- Yes?

126
00:09:53,353 --> 00:09:55,202
I'm Seo In Uk.

127
00:09:57,023 --> 00:09:59,332
It says Jaden.

128
00:09:59,332 --> 00:10:01,000
I'm Jaden too.

129
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,202
I see.

130
00:10:03,202 --> 00:10:05,940
What does a film company want with me?

131
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:09,655
Ju Yi Jae is still owed payment.

132
00:10:09,655 --> 00:10:11,568
Ju Yi Jae?

133
00:10:11,568 --> 00:10:13,095
What?

134
00:10:13,095 --> 00:10:14,451
How do you know her?

135
00:10:14,451 --> 00:10:17,058
She signed with us.

136
00:10:17,058 --> 00:10:19,388
In a way, I guess we owe you.

137
00:10:19,388 --> 00:10:23,773
We'd been dying to sign her.

138
00:10:23,773 --> 00:10:26,501
- But loose ends still need tying up.
- Wait...

139
00:10:26,501 --> 00:10:28,611
What did she sign?

140
00:10:28,611 --> 00:10:29,875
And tie up what?

141
00:10:29,875 --> 00:10:34,568
There must've been some mix-up.
I'll look into it first...

142
00:10:34,568 --> 00:10:36,125
No, no.

143
00:10:36,125 --> 00:10:37,953
You'd handle that yourself?

144
00:10:37,953 --> 00:10:40,865
Even your own work was too much trouble.

145
00:10:40,865 --> 00:10:43,002
What are you talking about?

146
00:10:43,002 --> 00:10:45,665
Is that what Yi Jae said?

147
00:10:46,255 --> 00:10:49,798
She's spreading lies because she's bitter.

148
00:10:49,798 --> 00:10:52,635
I'm not like that. You've got me wrong.

149
00:10:52,635 --> 00:10:55,836
No standard contract.
Driving for you. Editing for you.

150
00:10:55,836 --> 00:10:57,593
Clock-ins. Meetings.

151
00:10:57,593 --> 00:11:02,762
You gave unfair work to a contract worker,
then wrongfully fired her.

152
00:11:04,813 --> 00:11:07,571
Our legal team is good.

153
00:11:07,571 --> 00:11:10,537
They made it simple...

154
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,077
so you won't be bothered.

155
00:11:14,077 --> 00:11:15,822
Take a look.

156
00:11:16,859 --> 00:11:18,677
What's that paper?

157
00:11:21,817 --> 00:11:23,136
Yeah?

158
00:11:42,765 --> 00:11:45,875
Think of this as a warm-up
until the studio is ready.

159
00:11:45,875 --> 00:11:47,641
- Don't push yourself.
- No.

160
00:11:47,641 --> 00:11:53,615
This amazing work setup
is bringing my creative soul back to life.

161
00:11:58,613 --> 00:12:00,430
[One Hour Later]

162
00:12:01,523 --> 00:12:04,481
It has been dead for a while.

163
00:12:07,002 --> 00:12:08,438
Even old sparks can come back.

164
00:12:08,438 --> 00:12:11,451
Why don't you start by watching some movies?

165
00:12:11,451 --> 00:12:14,377
References. Very important.

166
00:12:19,953 --> 00:12:21,435
[Lead Actor, Go Sang Yeon]

167
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:26,404
Is he ever on time?

168
00:12:26,404 --> 00:12:28,298
There he is.

169
00:12:28,976 --> 00:12:31,374
He's not ready yet. Could you wait?

170
00:12:31,374 --> 00:12:33,094
He's already late.

171
00:12:33,094 --> 00:12:35,258
- Now you want more time?
- Sorry.

172
00:12:35,258 --> 00:12:37,553
It's my fault.

173
00:12:37,553 --> 00:12:39,890
You always cut Oh Ha Na slack.

174
00:12:39,890 --> 00:12:41,784
Why so hard on me?

175
00:12:41,784 --> 00:12:44,788
Just get me ready during rehearsal.

176
00:12:44,788 --> 00:12:48,008
Use someone close enough.

177
00:12:48,008 --> 00:12:49,092
Hey!

178
00:12:49,092 --> 00:12:51,425
Hey! You. White shirt.

179
00:12:51,425 --> 00:12:53,929
- Come here.
- Go on.

180
00:12:56,381 --> 00:12:58,011
- Me?
- Yeah.

181
00:12:58,011 --> 00:13:00,504
Here. Scene 26.

182
00:13:00,504 --> 00:13:02,433
Rehearse for me.

183
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:05,219
Good luck, Oh Ha Na.

184
00:13:08,632 --> 00:13:09,762
Cut!

185
00:13:09,762 --> 00:13:11,816
Okay!

186
00:13:11,816 --> 00:13:13,647
You're really good.

187
00:13:13,647 --> 00:13:17,061
It was just rehearsal, but I want to use that.

188
00:13:17,061 --> 00:13:18,831
How long have you acted?

189
00:13:18,831 --> 00:13:21,351
- I'd love to see you in my next project.
- Thank you.

190
00:13:21,351 --> 00:13:25,038
You've got the look and the emotion.

191
00:13:25,038 --> 00:13:26,548
Hey!

192
00:13:26,548 --> 00:13:28,448
Follow me.

193
00:13:33,325 --> 00:13:35,637
There he goes again.

194
00:13:35,637 --> 00:13:37,376
Beats me.

195
00:13:37,376 --> 00:13:39,480
He's been on edge lately.

196
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:41,386
It's not his first time.

197
00:13:41,386 --> 00:13:43,620
Why take it out on him?

198
00:13:49,326 --> 00:13:51,648
What's with you?

199
00:13:51,648 --> 00:13:54,226
- You laughed at me earlier.
- I didn't.

200
00:13:54,226 --> 00:13:59,233
They call me box-office poison,
so I'm a joke to you too?

201
00:13:59,233 --> 00:14:02,950
- I didn't.
- I can see it in your eyes.

202
00:14:02,950 --> 00:14:04,610
Saw your chance?

203
00:14:04,610 --> 00:14:06,160
Eyeing my spot?

204
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:08,039
I didn't.

205
00:14:08,039 --> 00:14:10,959
- You told me to, senior.
- "Senior?"

206
00:14:10,959 --> 00:14:13,087
Since when am I your senior?

207
00:14:13,775 --> 00:14:16,755
That's enough, Mr. Go.

208
00:14:16,755 --> 00:14:18,846
"Mr. Go?"

209
00:14:18,846 --> 00:14:20,443
You've got guts.

210
00:14:20,443 --> 00:14:22,449
Show some respect.

211
00:14:25,263 --> 00:14:27,756
I'll leave if you're done.

212
00:14:27,756 --> 00:14:29,583
Look at this punk.

213
00:14:29,583 --> 00:14:32,107
You're nothing.

214
00:14:32,107 --> 00:14:34,593
So why are you standing so tall?

215
00:14:34,593 --> 00:14:36,464
Who's behind you?

216
00:14:36,464 --> 00:14:39,321
Got some rich lady backing you?

217
00:14:39,321 --> 00:14:41,596
Any problem?

218
00:14:48,110 --> 00:14:50,961
- Have you lost it?
- You have.

219
00:14:50,961 --> 00:14:52,471
What...

220
00:14:52,471 --> 00:14:54,048
You two a thing?

221
00:14:54,048 --> 00:14:55,925
Yeah, we're close.

222
00:14:55,925 --> 00:14:58,569
- Who are you to touch my friend?
- "Friend?"

223
00:14:58,569 --> 00:15:01,070
You don't have friends.
You barely went to school.

224
00:15:01,070 --> 00:15:02,741
Why wouldn't I?

225
00:15:02,741 --> 00:15:05,776
- Didn't you watch "Ha Na's High School?"
- You only clocked in on shoot days.

226
00:15:05,776 --> 00:15:09,752
- It's called "going to school," idiot.
- With cameras?

227
00:15:09,752 --> 00:15:13,075
I heard some great stories
from your high school days.

228
00:15:13,075 --> 00:15:15,099
Your friends must've hated you.

229
00:15:15,099 --> 00:15:17,269
- What?
- Oh, right.

230
00:15:17,269 --> 00:15:21,677
Not your friends. Your bullying victims.

231
00:15:23,216 --> 00:15:24,826
I apologized for that!

232
00:15:24,826 --> 00:15:28,004
People don't change.

233
00:15:28,004 --> 00:15:31,081
You should've outgrown the bully act back then.

234
00:15:31,081 --> 00:15:34,009
I dropped out after middle school.

235
00:15:35,754 --> 00:15:38,490
Real classy, asshole.

236
00:15:39,204 --> 00:15:41,524
Come on, friend. Let's go.

237
00:15:42,604 --> 00:15:43,908
Where are you going?

238
00:15:43,908 --> 00:15:45,914
Get back here!

239
00:15:45,914 --> 00:15:48,152
That's hot!

240
00:15:48,152 --> 00:15:50,319
She didn't put it out!

241
00:15:50,319 --> 00:15:52,783
Where's my manager? Report her!

242
00:15:52,783 --> 00:15:54,299
Hot!

243
00:19:10,166 --> 00:19:12,932
<i>Why did I close my eyes?</i>

244
00:19:27,647 --> 00:19:28,977
What?

245
00:19:28,977 --> 00:19:31,526
You want me to keep going?

246
00:19:32,403 --> 00:19:34,947
No, I don't.

247
00:19:34,947 --> 00:19:36,472
But...

248
00:19:38,841 --> 00:19:40,298
Gosh.

249
00:19:44,094 --> 00:19:45,931
Good night.

250
00:19:45,931 --> 00:19:47,956
Yeah. Good night.

251
00:19:47,956 --> 00:19:49,760
Yeah. Bye.

252
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:51,159
Bye.

253
00:20:14,465 --> 00:20:15,769
Wait.

254
00:20:15,769 --> 00:20:18,040
Why is he sleeping here?

255
00:20:24,327 --> 00:20:26,060
[In Uk]
<i>Coming back?</i>

256
00:20:27,211 --> 00:20:29,542
<i>Not coming back.</i>

257
00:21:20,513 --> 00:21:23,173
- Morning.
- Good morning.

258
00:21:34,086 --> 00:21:36,643
Looks like you didn't sleep well.

259
00:21:36,643 --> 00:21:38,289
Yeah...

260
00:21:40,707 --> 00:21:42,374
Eat up.

261
00:21:48,829 --> 00:21:50,666
No coffee?

262
00:22:07,181 --> 00:22:08,907
Think.

263
00:22:19,526 --> 00:22:21,403
[Nan Young's gaze turns toward Moo Gyeom]

264
00:22:37,082 --> 00:22:40,819
[Nothing's coming to me... Nothing]

265
00:22:43,087 --> 00:22:45,466
[Woo Soo Bin]
<i>Did you eat?</i>

266
00:22:45,466 --> 00:22:48,060
[Want to have lunch later?]
[Don't push yourself too hard]

267
00:22:48,060 --> 00:22:51,515
[Are you eating properly?]
[You worked hard today. Sleep well]

268
00:23:02,366 --> 00:23:04,044
Come on...

269
00:23:04,044 --> 00:23:08,450
Retirement feels so empty.

270
00:23:08,450 --> 00:23:10,434
I'm still perfectly fine.

271
00:23:10,434 --> 00:23:12,137
Why kick me out?

272
00:23:12,137 --> 00:23:15,176
Tell me about it.

273
00:23:15,791 --> 00:23:19,928
Young guys move up,
and suddenly we're old news.

274
00:23:19,928 --> 00:23:23,846
Those young punks...

275
00:23:30,335 --> 00:23:31,814
Well, not always.

276
00:23:31,814 --> 00:23:34,794
Youth unemployment is terrible too.

277
00:23:34,794 --> 00:23:38,360
Plenty of them just goof off all day.

278
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:41,905
Kids these days have it too easy.

279
00:23:41,905 --> 00:23:44,176
- Enough. Stop.
- Why?

280
00:23:52,873 --> 00:23:54,757
I'm not just goofing off.

281
00:23:54,757 --> 00:23:57,151
I'm struggling, sir.

282
00:24:06,952 --> 00:24:08,056
Yu Geon.

283
00:24:08,056 --> 00:24:10,183
That event you mentioned.

284
00:24:10,183 --> 00:24:12,126
Did they find someone?

285
00:24:14,427 --> 00:24:16,334
You said you were busy writing.

286
00:24:16,334 --> 00:24:17,727
Yu Geon.

287
00:24:17,727 --> 00:24:19,457
Will you be in my movie?

288
00:24:19,457 --> 00:24:23,057
Come on. You know I hate that.

289
00:24:23,057 --> 00:24:26,707
Please don't give me even a tiny role.

290
00:24:26,707 --> 00:24:27,737
[Staff Only]

291
00:24:27,737 --> 00:24:29,326
- Hello.
- Yeah...

292
00:24:29,326 --> 00:24:31,770
I figured.

293
00:24:31,770 --> 00:24:32,886
Don't worry.

294
00:24:32,886 --> 00:24:37,299
Tiny role or not, I can't even do my own job.

295
00:24:37,299 --> 00:24:42,445
I can't write a single word,
so I'm here to make some cash.

296
00:24:43,097 --> 00:24:45,594
What does Soo Bin say?

297
00:24:45,594 --> 00:24:47,934
I'm dodging him.

298
00:24:47,934 --> 00:24:49,664
What am I going to do?

299
00:24:49,664 --> 00:24:53,239
I tell myself it's fine, but I can't calm down.

300
00:24:53,239 --> 00:24:56,383
That blinking cursor makes my heart race.

301
00:24:56,383 --> 00:24:57,913
And most of all...

302
00:24:57,913 --> 00:25:01,247
I'm scared Soo Bin will be disappointed.

303
00:25:01,944 --> 00:25:04,150
You must want to impress him.

304
00:25:06,273 --> 00:25:07,853
Good luck.

305
00:25:20,671 --> 00:25:22,373
Ju Yi Jae.

306
00:25:30,781 --> 00:25:32,601
Ju Yi Jae!

307
00:25:59,209 --> 00:26:01,251
Get in.

308
00:26:16,934 --> 00:26:18,074
Do you read the comments?

309
00:26:18,074 --> 00:26:19,575
[Something's off]
[They freeze when they lock eyes]

310
00:26:20,229 --> 00:26:22,038
You think viewers are stupid?

311
00:26:22,038 --> 00:26:24,968
Everyone can tell you two hate each other!

312
00:26:24,968 --> 00:26:26,468
You kicked his shin?

313
00:26:26,468 --> 00:26:27,626
Burned him with a cigarette?

314
00:26:27,626 --> 00:26:30,311
Why should I hear that crap from Hyeon Gu?

315
00:26:30,311 --> 00:26:32,335
Who's Hyeon Gu?

316
00:26:32,335 --> 00:26:34,292
Sang Yeon's CEO!

317
00:26:34,292 --> 00:26:37,250
Stop picking fights with him.

318
00:26:37,250 --> 00:26:39,712
Handling your costar is part of the job.

319
00:26:39,712 --> 00:26:43,152
Why do you clash with every rom-com lead?

320
00:26:43,152 --> 00:26:47,149
They start it. They try to put me in my place.

321
00:26:47,149 --> 00:26:50,636
- What?
- They all think they're kings.

322
00:26:50,636 --> 00:26:53,172
But you know what's worse?

323
00:26:53,172 --> 00:26:56,143
To everyone else,
I probably look just like them.

324
00:26:56,143 --> 00:26:59,067
So what? Just stay with your own kind.

325
00:26:59,067 --> 00:27:01,667
Don't come down and get your feet dirty.

326
00:27:01,667 --> 00:27:02,820
And...

327
00:27:02,820 --> 00:27:07,161
Isn't that a little hypocritical
on your way to a luxury event?

328
00:27:08,974 --> 00:27:10,218
- Director Kang!
- Yes.

329
00:27:10,218 --> 00:27:13,718
- Drop me at the next intersection!
- The next intersection?

330
00:27:13,718 --> 00:27:14,988
- Over there...
- Yeah.

331
00:27:14,988 --> 00:27:18,173
We're in the left lane, but I'll try.

332
00:27:27,506 --> 00:27:30,730
Hello. Please try this scent.

333
00:27:30,730 --> 00:27:31,951
Thank you.

334
00:27:31,951 --> 00:27:35,206
Hello. Please try this scent.

335
00:27:37,722 --> 00:27:39,398
Thank you.

336
00:27:40,224 --> 00:27:42,476
Hello. Try this...

337
00:27:44,971 --> 00:27:46,971
Why'd you skip me?

338
00:27:48,964 --> 00:27:52,127
- At least act happy to see me.
- I'm not.

339
00:27:52,127 --> 00:27:53,705
Ever heard of manners?

340
00:27:53,705 --> 00:27:55,788
Depends on you.

341
00:27:59,997 --> 00:28:02,196
There's someone I'm happy to see.

342
00:28:06,766 --> 00:28:08,964
What's with you two?

343
00:28:08,964 --> 00:28:10,804
Is he your manager?

344
00:28:12,020 --> 00:28:13,757
Are you... my manager?

345
00:28:13,757 --> 00:28:15,817
No. I meant you.

346
00:28:15,817 --> 00:28:18,734
- Me?
- You're pretty casual.

347
00:28:18,734 --> 00:28:20,769
So are you.

348
00:28:21,577 --> 00:28:25,747
Your Korean is perfect.
Why only speak English at the audition?

349
00:28:25,747 --> 00:28:29,518
Because it was in America. And this is Korea.

350
00:28:30,984 --> 00:28:32,752
Are you close with him?

351
00:28:32,752 --> 00:28:35,282
No. He's obviously older than me.

352
00:28:35,282 --> 00:28:38,807
We were just neighbors for a bit as kids.

353
00:28:38,807 --> 00:28:40,476
"Neighbors?"

354
00:28:40,476 --> 00:28:41,801
"For a bit?"

355
00:28:41,801 --> 00:28:44,181
Never be his friend.

356
00:28:57,485 --> 00:28:58,801
How do you know her?

357
00:28:58,801 --> 00:29:01,195
- Curious?
- Yes.

358
00:29:01,195 --> 00:29:02,674
I'm a director.

359
00:29:02,674 --> 00:29:03,870
She's an actress.

360
00:29:03,870 --> 00:29:06,099
That's it.

361
00:29:06,099 --> 00:29:08,719
At least we're not neighbors.

362
00:29:08,719 --> 00:29:10,681
That's not the way.

363
00:29:10,681 --> 00:29:12,440
You know where I'm going?

364
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:14,741
Aren't you buying anything?

365
00:29:14,741 --> 00:29:17,398
- Will you give me a discount?
- Fine.

366
00:29:18,793 --> 00:29:21,097
- You like Rouvee, right?
- Yes!

367
00:29:21,097 --> 00:29:22,762
- You like it, right?
- Yes!

368
00:29:22,762 --> 00:29:25,377
Raise your hand if you do!

369
00:29:25,377 --> 00:29:28,037
If you love Rouvee, make some noise!

370
00:29:29,709 --> 00:29:33,086
Next up is the moment
you've all been waiting for.

371
00:29:33,086 --> 00:29:37,069
It's time for the lucky draw!

372
00:29:38,099 --> 00:29:41,630
This lucky draw will be picked
by our brand model,

373
00:29:41,630 --> 00:29:45,018
actress Oh Ha Na herself.

374
00:29:45,018 --> 00:29:49,452
Please welcome actress Oh Ha Na to the stage!

375
00:29:49,452 --> 00:29:51,715
Actress Oh Ha Na!

376
00:29:59,698 --> 00:30:03,166
I don't often get to meet fans this close.

377
00:30:03,166 --> 00:30:06,737
Let's have fun today.

378
00:30:08,041 --> 00:30:11,464
Who will be our lucky winner?

379
00:30:12,470 --> 00:30:14,501
- Number 38.
- Number 38!

380
00:30:14,501 --> 00:30:16,494
It's me! It's me!

381
00:30:20,979 --> 00:30:22,981
- Next is number 4.
- Number 4!

382
00:30:22,981 --> 00:30:24,114
Who is it?

383
00:30:24,114 --> 00:30:27,391
Number 4! Congrats!

384
00:30:28,243 --> 00:30:30,880
Please pick the last number.

385
00:30:30,880 --> 00:30:33,317
Last one! Last one!

386
00:30:33,317 --> 00:30:34,521
- Last one!
- Last one!

387
00:30:34,521 --> 00:30:36,913
Raise your hand if you want it!

388
00:31:39,329 --> 00:31:41,348
Sorry!

389
00:31:43,230 --> 00:31:44,515
Who are you?

390
00:31:44,515 --> 00:31:47,724
- Do you know me?
- This one's for you.

391
00:31:47,724 --> 00:31:50,117
The other one, I got bullied into buying.

392
00:31:50,117 --> 00:31:51,374
I get why now.

393
00:31:51,374 --> 00:31:54,965
Do you know me or not?

394
00:31:54,965 --> 00:31:56,855
I know who you are.

395
00:31:56,855 --> 00:31:59,172
And I know why you're here.

396
00:32:05,850 --> 00:32:08,889
Aren't you even mad?

397
00:32:14,168 --> 00:32:17,674
You finally made up your mind,

398
00:32:18,599 --> 00:32:22,092
but it didn't go the way you wanted. Right?

399
00:32:22,092 --> 00:32:24,946
You must've been scared.

400
00:32:24,946 --> 00:32:27,287
But that's normal.

401
00:32:30,390 --> 00:32:34,733
I'm scared too, that I'm just being selfish.

402
00:32:34,733 --> 00:32:39,196
What if I'm only making things harder for you?

403
00:32:41,074 --> 00:32:45,033
But we're trying to do something great.

404
00:32:49,119 --> 00:32:50,692
Yi Jae.

405
00:32:51,525 --> 00:32:57,134
Greatness isn't about making something amazing.

406
00:32:59,713 --> 00:33:02,255
Going all the way together,

407
00:33:02,255 --> 00:33:04,384
that's what makes it great.

408
00:33:10,099 --> 00:33:12,382
Studio tomorrow, right?

409
00:33:13,141 --> 00:33:17,978
Think hard about
whether you're with me to the end.

410
00:33:21,360 --> 00:33:22,993
I should go.

411
00:34:03,013 --> 00:34:07,194
<i>Greatness isn't about making something amazing.</i>

412
00:34:08,738 --> 00:34:11,378
<i>Going all the way together,</i>

413
00:34:11,378 --> 00:34:13,405
<i>that's what makes it great.</i>

414
00:35:12,386 --> 00:35:13,953
Okay.

415
00:35:26,068 --> 00:35:27,873
Woo Soo Bin?

416
00:35:29,279 --> 00:35:30,896
It's you, right?

417
00:35:32,464 --> 00:35:34,034
Thank God.

418
00:35:34,034 --> 00:35:36,508
I've been looking everywhere.

419
00:35:36,508 --> 00:35:38,074
You're late.

420
00:35:38,074 --> 00:35:39,665
Trunk!

421
00:35:39,665 --> 00:35:41,095
Yeah.

422
00:35:48,062 --> 00:35:49,843
I'll load it.

423
00:35:59,140 --> 00:36:01,738
Let's go. To do something great.

424
00:36:09,166 --> 00:36:11,284
This is so nice, huh?

425
00:36:11,284 --> 00:36:13,738
- Yeah.
- The ocean is wonderful.

426
00:36:13,738 --> 00:36:15,177
Right.

427
00:36:24,117 --> 00:36:26,532
- What should we eat?
- Anything's fine.

428
00:36:26,532 --> 00:36:29,004
I know a great bibimbap place.

429
00:36:29,004 --> 00:36:30,355
Bibimbap?

430
00:36:30,355 --> 00:36:32,554
Not bibimbap.

431
00:36:32,554 --> 00:36:34,661
- Something else.
- What do you even like?

432
00:36:34,661 --> 00:36:36,246
- Remember this place?
- Where?

433
00:36:36,246 --> 00:36:38,304
- There.
- Oh, there.

434
00:36:38,304 --> 00:36:42,337
- You don't remember, huh?
- Of course I do.

435
00:36:46,690 --> 00:36:48,403
I'm excited.

436
00:37:30,442 --> 00:37:32,262
Come on.

437
00:37:33,677 --> 00:37:34,883
Mom.

438
00:37:34,883 --> 00:37:36,283
What?

439
00:37:36,283 --> 00:37:38,307
What do you want me to be?

440
00:37:38,307 --> 00:37:40,157
A decent human being.

441
00:37:40,157 --> 00:37:41,590
Agreed.

442
00:37:42,628 --> 00:37:44,313
Stop joking.

443
00:37:44,313 --> 00:37:46,310
Anything.

444
00:37:46,310 --> 00:37:49,691
I'm not asking what's for dinner.

445
00:37:49,691 --> 00:37:52,548
At least I can choose dinner.

446
00:37:52,548 --> 00:37:56,201
Kids never turn out the way you want.

447
00:37:56,201 --> 00:37:58,185
Treasure them? Adore them?

448
00:37:58,185 --> 00:38:00,916
What a joke.

449
00:38:01,846 --> 00:38:03,522
That's harsh to your fired daughter.

450
00:38:03,522 --> 00:38:06,466
You were always working yourself to death.

451
00:38:06,466 --> 00:38:07,722
It's for the best.

452
00:38:07,722 --> 00:38:09,747
Just find something else.

453
00:38:09,747 --> 00:38:14,603
You could work festivals nationwide
and still make a living.

454
00:38:14,603 --> 00:38:16,133
Just buy a car.

455
00:38:16,133 --> 00:38:18,307
Stop taking the bus.

456
00:38:19,366 --> 00:38:20,811
Mom.

457
00:38:21,660 --> 00:38:24,107
I came here to write.

458
00:38:25,078 --> 00:38:26,301
What?

459
00:38:26,301 --> 00:38:27,436
A movie.

460
00:38:27,436 --> 00:38:29,436
I want to try again.

461
00:38:32,793 --> 00:38:35,280
Here we go again.

462
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,901
I told you so many times.

463
00:38:36,901 --> 00:38:41,559
That's for rich kids
with nothing to worry about.

464
00:38:42,389 --> 00:38:45,164
So Woo Soo Bin can, but I can't?

465
00:38:45,164 --> 00:38:46,891
Right.

466
00:38:46,891 --> 00:38:49,454
He went all the way to America and made it.

467
00:38:49,454 --> 00:38:52,107
His dad was against it, so he cut him off.

468
00:38:52,107 --> 00:38:56,710
That courage comes from
having something to fall back on.

469
00:38:57,725 --> 00:38:59,262
No wonder I live like this.

470
00:38:59,262 --> 00:39:02,224
Fine. I'll live my own life.

471
00:39:06,462 --> 00:39:08,346
Don't tell me this is because of him.

472
00:39:08,346 --> 00:39:10,076
I already signed.

473
00:39:10,076 --> 00:39:11,632
I'm doing it with him.

474
00:39:11,632 --> 00:39:12,686
You little...

475
00:39:12,686 --> 00:39:14,986
Are you out of your mind?

476
00:39:14,986 --> 00:39:17,039
Anyone but him!

477
00:39:17,039 --> 00:39:18,907
Look what he did to you!

478
00:39:18,907 --> 00:39:19,983
Why?

479
00:39:19,983 --> 00:39:23,143
Because he's rich and I'm poor.
It's not his fault.

480
00:39:23,143 --> 00:39:26,673
If you're right, I should've left home.

481
00:39:26,673 --> 00:39:30,413
Family or not, I should've lived my life!

482
00:39:30,413 --> 00:39:33,328
What is that supposed to mean?

483
00:39:59,458 --> 00:40:01,515
Ju Yi Jae, come out.

484
00:40:01,515 --> 00:40:03,436
Hey.

485
00:40:04,263 --> 00:40:06,304
Eat breakfast!

486
00:40:21,945 --> 00:40:24,116
[Interbank Transfer: Security Deposit]

487
00:40:30,748 --> 00:40:33,957
Gosh! You scared me.

488
00:40:33,957 --> 00:40:35,875
- When did you get here?
- At dawn.

489
00:40:35,875 --> 00:40:37,275
Why?

490
00:40:38,078 --> 00:40:39,981
I ran away.

491
00:40:40,617 --> 00:40:42,133
What?

492
00:40:47,441 --> 00:40:50,572
We're adapting the original draft.

493
00:40:50,572 --> 00:40:55,482
Updating a ten-year-old draft won't be easy.

494
00:40:55,482 --> 00:40:57,935
So let's start with the structure.

495
00:40:57,935 --> 00:41:02,098
So I broke it down by chapter and scene.

496
00:41:02,098 --> 00:41:03,589
When did you do all that?

497
00:41:03,589 --> 00:41:05,672
Whenever I could.

498
00:41:05,672 --> 00:41:07,018
You called that warming up?

499
00:41:07,018 --> 00:41:09,419
Even if we change lines or move scenes,

500
00:41:09,419 --> 00:41:11,755
the framework will hold.

501
00:41:12,961 --> 00:41:16,118
Are we really doing this every time?

502
00:41:16,118 --> 00:41:19,421
Sharing every word, comma, and period?

503
00:41:19,421 --> 00:41:20,844
Yes.

504
00:41:24,688 --> 00:41:26,118
<i>Seriously?</i>

505
00:41:26,118 --> 00:41:27,782
<i>I'm so embarrassed.</i>

506
00:41:27,782 --> 00:41:30,221
<i>It shows too much.</i>

507
00:41:30,221 --> 00:41:32,292
It's not a diary.

508
00:41:32,292 --> 00:41:35,306
This is efficient. We can sync in real time.

509
00:41:35,306 --> 00:41:38,316
I wanted to clean it up before showing you.

510
00:41:38,316 --> 00:41:40,108
Ju Yi Jae.

511
00:41:40,108 --> 00:41:42,483
We're co-writing this.

512
00:41:42,483 --> 00:41:44,700
We need to write as one.

513
00:41:44,700 --> 00:41:47,619
Until even we can't tell who wrote which scene.

514
00:41:47,619 --> 00:41:49,713
Okay, I'll catch up fast.

515
00:41:49,713 --> 00:41:51,510
Let's meet whenever we need to.

516
00:41:51,510 --> 00:41:53,157
And eat together.

517
00:41:53,157 --> 00:41:55,238
Share schedules too.

518
00:41:56,237 --> 00:41:57,900
Want to work out together?

519
00:41:57,900 --> 00:41:59,220
For efficiency.

520
00:41:59,220 --> 00:42:00,330
No, thank you.

521
00:42:00,330 --> 00:42:03,028
Let's skip the workouts.

522
00:42:04,845 --> 00:42:07,213
- Let's start.
- Yeah.

523
00:42:07,811 --> 00:42:10,607
- I'll share the file first.
- Okay.

524
00:42:33,606 --> 00:42:34,743
<i>"Nan Young."</i>

525
00:42:34,743 --> 00:42:36,987
<i>"Graceful and proud."</i>

526
00:42:36,987 --> 00:42:40,096
<i>"Noble Young Master."</i>

527
00:42:40,096 --> 00:42:43,875
<i>"You are quite impatient."</i>

528
00:42:46,608 --> 00:42:47,898
<i>"Nan Young."</i>

529
00:42:47,898 --> 00:42:50,907
<i>"She tries to pull away."</i>

530
00:42:50,907 --> 00:42:56,850
<i>"Just then, Moo Gyeom pulls her by the waist."</i>

531
00:43:00,436 --> 00:43:02,169
<i>"Moo Gyeom."</i>

532
00:43:02,169 --> 00:43:05,535
<i>"Why shouldn't I be?"</i>

533
00:43:05,535 --> 00:43:10,120
<i>"When your eyes are so full of love for me."</i>

534
00:43:13,905 --> 00:43:15,608
I like it.

535
00:43:23,541 --> 00:43:26,519
What? You only worked?

536
00:43:26,519 --> 00:43:27,883
How do you only work?

537
00:43:27,883 --> 00:43:29,502
Weren't you nervous?

538
00:43:29,502 --> 00:43:32,003
Nervous, my ass.

539
00:43:32,003 --> 00:43:33,347
Hey.

540
00:43:33,347 --> 00:43:34,771
I'm Ju Yi Jae.

541
00:43:34,771 --> 00:43:36,350
I'm not that easy.

542
00:43:36,350 --> 00:43:38,751
This isn't about being easy.

543
00:43:38,751 --> 00:43:41,020
A grown man and woman under one roof?

544
00:43:41,020 --> 00:43:43,223
What genre is that?

545
00:43:43,223 --> 00:43:46,433
Usually, romance.

546
00:43:46,433 --> 00:43:48,081
Wait.

547
